VLand Rover Ranage Rover Evoque\u000a is perhaps the best-selling SUV model built by the British Luxury car brand JLR. Ever since it arrived in India, its hasn't lost the steam and is continuing its success run pertaining to its sales. Now, this contemporary SUV has received a facelift with several new cosmetics and features. With regards to the technical specifications, its power source is the same SD4 diesel engine, whose displacement capacity 2179cc. Its transmission duties are taken care by a 9-speed automatic gearbox that supports 4WD drive mechanism. As for the variant line-up, this latest version now comes in four trims like Pure, SE, HSE and HSE Dynamic. Many expected this SUV series to come with the company's latest TD4 oil-burner, which is currently available in global markets. However, the manufacturer has opted to offer this new drive-train from 2016. This new generation product gets a handful of changes to its exteriors with an updated radiator grille, bigger air vents, redesigned headlamps and taillights. Also, we can see an updated bonnet with scoops, which were present only in its 3-door versions earlier. The interior section remains largely unchanged, expect for some changes with regards to the equipments. Also, we can see that the seats are completely new, which only helps to improve driving comfort. All the trims in the series are now being given with an 8-inch InControl touchscreen infotainment system as standard system. While the top end version also gets an InControl Plus technology as additional feature.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000aMoving on to the features front, it gets several new facilities like a heads-up display, surround camera system, panoramic sunroof, rear seat entertainment package and mood lighting. Also, it gets a hand-free tail-gate opening facility that helps owners to open the back door by waving the foot under the rear bumper. Other notable feature are the Terrain Response System, which is given as a standard feature across all its trims. Besides these, all the other features have been retained from its previous version. In terms of safety, it gets crucial protective aspects like airbags for enhanced safety, hill descent control, engine immobilizer, Range Rover Smart Key Controls and hazard warning lights under heavy braking. This vehicle will be rivaling with the likes of Audi Q5, BMW X3 and Volvo XC60 in the Indian SUV market. Currently, it is available with a standard warranty of three years or 100000 Kilometers, whichever comes first.The 2016 version of Range Rover Evoque carries subtle changes on its exteriors and commands a more opulent persona. Its retains the same body structure from its predecessor and yet, it looks much more advanced and modern. Its front facade being modified with a new radiator grille rendering it a sporty appeal. The headlight cluster too gets a new design that looks much more crisp and clear. The front bumper got bigger in size with pronounced air inlets. Furthermore, they are fitted with fog light strips that amplifies this facet. The lower section of this bumper is fitted with a black colored stripe along with a nudge guard providing additional protection on rugged roads. One of the notable changes it gets is that the bonnet is now designed with scoops, which further enhances its dynamic appeal. Moreover, the "RANGE ROVER" lettering on it adds to its stylish appearance. The side profile remains identical to its outgoing version. It has chrome lining on window sill, glossy black finish for pillars, and body colored for door handles. Also, it gets body colored outside rear view mirrors with integrated turn blinkers. Its wheel arches look much bigger and they are paired with a set of newly designed alloy wheels. As for the rear section, we can notice that the taillights are modified and have been integrated with LED brake lights for illumination. Apart from this, its bumper too received some changes, which compliments its overall new look. It has an expressive tailgate that is affixed with a chrome plated strip and 'Range Rover' lettering on it.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000aExterior Measurements:\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000aThis latest model series has a total length measuring 4370mm and a height of about 1635mm. Its total width including mirrors measures about 2090mm. However, the wheelbase is just about 2660mm, which is not too long or short. This SUV has a wading depth of 500mm and an approach angle of 25 degrees, which is quite good for an off-roader.Ed's take: \u000a The interiors of the Range Rover Evoque are a great blend of technology and fashion. The Evoque is more of a fashion icon vehicle and the exterior design says so. Designers have done a terrific job for the interior as well.\u000a As for its interiors, the seats have been completely redesigned for a better traveling comfort. They are covered with luxurious leather upholstery that renders a magnificent appeal to the insides. Also some changes have been done to the dashboard for placing an advanced 8 inch touchscreen infotainment system. Besides this, no change or modification has been done to the cabin. Its plush cabin is quite spacious and can accommodate five people with ease. The cockpit has perhaps the best design that we can see in current generation SUVs. The steering wheel is another eye-catching factor, thanks to its four-spoke design and illuminated multi-functional switches. The car maker has done up its interiors with an ebony black color scheme that only renders an eye-soothing effect to the cabin. Furthermore, it is complemented by ambient lighting system. It has driver oriented cockpit with commanding driving position and ergonomically positioned control switches, which are easy to reach. The company has given it a number of utilities rear seat center armrest with two cup holders, load space cover, auto dimming interior rear view mirror, carpet mats with edging, push button start, memory function for driver's seat and a few other aspects that adds to its elegance.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000aInterior Comfort:\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000aThis latest version of Evoque is now available in four different variants such as Pure, SE, HSE and HSE Dynamic. To start with, its entry level 'Pure' trim comes with features like oxford leather cover for steering wheel, carpet mats with edging, illumination for foot-well, push-button engine start and an adjustable steering column. Its front seats can be manually adjusted in six different ways, which is an added feature. As for the convenience, this trim has facilities like automatic climate control unit featuring air filtration, global opening for all windows, luggage cover, cruise control system and rear seats with split folding facility. The next-in-line trim 'SE' has additional facilities like rain sensing windscreen wipers, automatic headlamps, auto-dimming interior mirror, front parking aid, smokers package, rear AC vents, covered central control stowage and sun-visors with illuminated vanity mirrors. Its 'HSE' trim has a few more advanced features like parking aid with rear camera including hitching guidance, customer configurable interior mood lighting, infotainment system featuring InControl Touch Plus technology, and 12/12 way electrically adjustable front seats. Furthermore, this trim also has electric outside mirrors that have several functions like heating, power fold, projected Evoque graphic and memory functions with auto dipping in reverse gear. The top-of-the-line HSE Dynamic also has same set of features, but it additionally gets a surround camera for parking assistance, keyless entry, proximity sensing and touch detection for overhead map lights.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000aInterior Measurements:\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000aThis stylish SUV looks compact from outside, but it is as spacious as any other SUV in its class and provides comfortable accommodation for five passengers. It has a spacious boot compartment and a massive fuel tank that can store upto 70 litres of fuel within.Ed' take: \u000a The acceleration of the diesel and petrol engine of the Evoque is good and it doesn\u2019t feel any smaller. The performance has gone notches above as it now has better performance thank to better gearing with the new nine-speed ZF transmission.\u000a The manufacturer has mated this power plant to a 9-speed automatic gearbox. This propels the vehicle to accelerate from 0 to 100 Kmph mark in a mere 8.5 seconds. At the same time, it can go up to a top speed of 195 Kmph.Ed's take: \u000a Considering mind over matter, then the 2.2-litre diesel engine is the most sensible buy as the petrol is expensive and is only available in 3-door.\u000a Under the hood of this Range Rover Evoque, lies a 2.2-litre SD4 oil-burner, which is the same mill that is currently performing in the outgoing model. It has a total of 4-cylinders that have a total of 16 valves in them. It has a displacement capacity of 2179cc. Based on a dual overhead camshaft valve configuration, this mill comes integrated with a turbocharger for a much better power output. It can churn out a maximum of 187.7bhp at 5200rpm in combination with a commanding torque output of 420Nm at 2000rpm. This drive train been mated to an advanced nine speed automatic transmission gearbox that distributes the engine power to all its four wheels. This sophisticated gearbox not just improves the performance, but it also reduces the fuel consumption by 20%.Ed''s take: \u000a The diesel engine of the Evoque is frugal despite having good performance. And now it has improved further as it is offered with a nine-speed ZF transmission.\u000a Currently, this new generation Evoque draws power from the same SD4 oil-burner sourced from Ford Motors. This mill has the common rail direct fuel injection technology helping it to deliver a mileage of approximately 12.7 Kmpl, under standard driving conditions.Ed's take: \u000a The Evoque gets the smallest engine from the JLR stable, which is the new 2.0-litre petrol. But the power rating of these engines is good.\u000a The 2.2-litre diesel engine is a 4-cylindered mill built with technology based on a DOHC valve configuration. It is also turbocharged for enhanced power output. This drive-train is capable of unleashing a peak power of 187.7bhp along with a torque of 420Nm.Ed's take: \u000a Being a luxury vehicle, the Evoque gets touchscreen music system, cruise control, ESP, premium leather.\u000a The manufacturer is currently offering all the trims with an advanced touchscreen infotainment system having an 8-inch high resolution display. It is integrated with a Land Rover Sound System and has a total of 8 speakers with 'InControl Touch'. Also include is a 5-inch TFT color driver information center that displays crucial information and keeps the driver informed. Besides this, there are connectivity features like USB, AUX-In and Bluetooth. The HSE trim also has an Autostrasse (Asia Nav) navigation system along with a 380W Meridian sound system as standard feature. In addition to these, we can also find a Head-up display that adds to the convenience of driver.Ed's take: \u000a The ride and handling characteristics of the Evoque are good, as the ride is plush like any Range Rover and the handling is just like a sedan\u000a This SUV has a reliable braking and suspension mechanism like we have seen in other Land Rover models. All its wheels are fitted with disc brakes featuring high performance calipers. Aiding this mechanism are the anti-lock braking system, electronic brake force distribution and emergency brake assist system that offers driver with superior control over the SUV. It also features cornering brake control, dynamic and roll stability control, electric parking brake and trailer stability assist function. On the other hand, the front and rear axles are assembled with an adaptive dynamic system that helps in reducing the impact of jerks and provide an exceptional driving experience. It is also integrated a highly resp