nput options. The smooth dashboard looks quite elegant and is integrated with a few equipments like a three spoke steering wheel, a large glove box, AC vents and so on. Other aspects in the cabin include foldable rear seat, air conditioning unit, multifunction steering wheel and some storage spaces as well.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000aApart from all these features, the car maker has given this SUV a lot of safety features, which gives the occupants a stress free driving experience. Some of these include dual front airbags, electronic traction control, high mount stop lamp, central locking system and many other such aspects. Besides these, it is offered with some innovative functions like Terrain Response 2 with auto setting, Torque Vectoring by braking, Dynamic Response and so on that adds to the convenience. This vehicle is competing against the likes of Mercedes Benz ML Class, Toyota Land Cruiser, Audi Q7 and others in this segment. The company offers it in some exciting body paint options for the customers to select from. It has a standard warranty of three years or 1,00,000 kilometers, whichever comes first. This period can be further extended at an additional cost. Moreover, it has 3-years warranty for paint work and six years protection for perforation of body work.This robust sports utility vehicle is huge in size and looks stunning in its contemporary body design. It is blessed with a light weight all-aluminum body structure with decent ground clearance, which makes it capable for off-roading. Starting with the front facade, it has an aggressive radiator grille that is very sleek and embedded with a prominent company logo in the center. This grille is surrounded by a trendy looking headlight cluster, which is integrated with halogen headlamps in the base level trim. While the remaining variants have Xenon headlamps along with automatic headlamp control function. The bonnet has a few visible character lines on it, which gives it a stylish appearance. There is a wide windscreen that is integrated with a couple of intermittent wipers. Besides these, it has a well sculpted bumper that includes a wide air dam, which helps in cooling the engine quickly. It is further flanked by a couple of fog lamps that not only adds to its attractiveness but also improves visibility during foggy climatic conditions. There is also a protective cladding fitted beneath the bumper, which adds to the safety quotient. The slanted bonnet has a couple of visible character lines and it is embossed with \u201cRange Rover\u201d lettering on it. Coming to its side profile, it has a boxy type of design but the expressive lines and wheel arch molding gives it a modish look. It has black colored window sill, while the door handles and outside rear view mirrors are painted in body color. Whereas, its wheel arches are equipped with an elegant set of 20 inch alloy wheels that further improves its appearance. The side profile also has wider vents with metallic straps that gives an upmarket feel. The rear end is muscular and includes a large boot lid engraved with model badging treated with chrome. It also has a thick horizontal strip as well as variant badging. There is a body colored bumper that has protective cladding fitted underneath it. Another aspect is the wide windscreen that is complimented by a spoiler and includes high mount stop as well.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000aExterior Measurements:\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000aThe renowned automaker has designed this vehicle with an overall length of 4850mm along with a total width of 2220mm, which includes both external rear view mirrors. It comes with a total height of 1780mm that ensures enough head space for all occupants. It has a large wheelbase of 2923mm, which is quite good and offers a spacious cabin inside. It is designed with a minimum ground clearance of 278mm, which makes it perfect for maneuvering on roughest terrains.Ed's Take:\u000a The interiors of the Range Rover Sport are derived from the Range Rover, however these are sporty with a bit harder seats and different gear knob. The instrument cluster too is different on the Range Rover Sport.\u000a The company has given this Land Rover Range Rover Sport have a contemporary look, which comes along with attractive design elements in it. The cabin is quite roomy and takes in five people with ease and offers ample space for a relaxing journey. It is beautifully decorated with a two tone color scheme that gives a pleasant feel to its passengers. The internal section includes several top class features that are not only useful but also offers convenience during the journey. There are high quality plastic materials used inside the cabin, which adds to its classy look. The manufacturers have worked maximum on designing its sporty cockpit, which includes a number of aspects that takes care of every requirement of the driver. There is smooth dashboard available, which is designed elegantly and houses a few equipments. These include a sporty steering wheel that is mounted with audio as well as phone control buttons, which makes it quite convenient for the driver. The central console is accentuated with silver inserts and has several buttons which are very neatly placed. Moreover, the dashboard is also integrated with an instrument cluster and a large glove box compartment that is good enough for placing small things at hand. There are wide and well cushioned seats incorporated, which are covered with premium cloth upholstery in its base level trim. The SE variant is blessed with Grained leather seat covers, while there is Oxford perforated leather upholstery used in the HSE trim. On the other hand, its top end variant is bestowed with Oxford perforated leather seat covers that has Autobiography pattern. The front seats can be adjusted in several ways depending upon the variant, while the rear seat comes with 60:40 split folding facility, which is useful to bring in more luggage. The door trims and panels in the S and SE trims have dark brushed aluminum inserts, while the HSE variant gets micro mesh aluminum finishing. On the other hand, these aspects have shadow zebrano wood veneer inserts in its high end trim, which makes its interiors look more appealing.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000aInterior Comfort:\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000aThis model series is incorporated with a number of sophisticated features, which makes it one of the comfortable vehicle in its segment. Its Autobiography trim is blessed with some unique comfort features such as 18/18 way electrically adjustable front seats with memory function and premium carpet mats with edging. It has 4-zone control automatic climate control unit, which can be adjusted according to the convenience. At the same time, its HSE trim has 14/14 way power adjustable front seats with memory function that adds to the convenience. It has 3-zone climate control unit, auto dimming interior rear view mirror and front center console with cooling compartment. While, the S and SE variants have 4-way and 6-adjustable front seats respectively. Both these variants are incorporated with an efficient air conditioning unit, which cools the cabin quickly. It also has an adaptive cruise control system that maintains a steady speed as set by the driver on the highways. It also has a leather wrapped steering wheel, which is mounted with audio, cruise and call control buttons for convenience of its driver. The top end diesel and petrol variants are blessed with an advanced Meridian surround sound audio system with single slot CD player, MP3 disc, file compatibility, USB interface and i-Pod port. One of the most important feature of its Autobiography variant is the presence of rear seat entertainment system with a high resolution 8-inch touch screen display that has several controls for convenience. While other variants have Range Rover audio system with eight speakers that enhances the ambiance of its cabin. It also supports Bluetooth connectivity for pairing the mobile phones along with audio streaming. This SUV is also equipped with a rear park distance sensors with visual display. The SE trim is bestowed with with rear view camera, while other two variants get surround camera system. Apart from these it is incorporated with luggage compartment with lashing eyes, glove box unit with cooling effect and 4-way manually adjustable steering column.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000aInterior Measurements:\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000aThis stylish sports utility vehicle is very spacious from inside and comes with a seating capacity five passengers. The wheelbase of 2923mm provides ample leg room, head and shoulder space. Its fuel tank capacity is 70 litres, which is quite good for planning longer drives. It has a spacious boot compartment that can be further increased up to 1761 litres by folding its second row seat.Ed's Take:\u000a The 5.0-litre V8 is the fastest Land Rover ever made. So, this speaks about how good the acceleration is.\u000a Both its engines are coupled with an eight speed automatic transmission gear box, which allows the diesel engine to attain a top speed of around 210 Kmph. At the same time, it can cross the speed barrier of 100 Kmph in just 7.2 seconds from a standstill, which is incredible for the occupants sitting inside the cabin. On the other hand, its petrol mill can achieve an impressive top speed of 225 Kmph approximately and accelerates from 0 to 100 Kmph in about 5.3 seconds.Ed's Take:\u000a The Range Rover Sport\u2019s 3.0-litre V6 also performed well, and it produces sufficient power not just drive but to overtake also. The petrol version is good for the track also.\u000a As said above, this Land Rover Range Rover Sport model series is available in both petrol and diesel engine options for the buyers to choose from. Its Autobiography trim is equipped with a powerful 5.0-litre petrol engine under the hood, which comes with a displacement capacity of 4999cc. It is integrated with eight cylinders and thirty two 