ower of 503bhp in the range of 6000 to 6500rpm. At the same time, it generates a maximum torque output of 625Nm that ranges between 2500 to 5500rpm that is good for Indian road conditions.Ed's Take:\u000a The Range Rover Sport comes loaded with brownies like in-dash system, Bluetooth connectivity, cameras for parking and off-roading, etc.\u000a The company has given the HSE and Autobiography variants of this sports utility vehicle an advanced Meridian surround sound audio system with single slot CD player, MP3 disc, file compatibility, USB interface along with i-Pod port and 19-speakers that enhances the ambiance of its entire cabin. While other trims get Range Rover music system with eight speakers. This music system of all these variants supports Bluetooth connectivity with audio streaming. The HSE and Autobiography trim also has rear seat entertainment with high resolution 8-inch touch screen display that has various controls for convenience. It also has a leather wrapped steering wheel, which is mounted with audio, cruise and call control buttons. This SUV is incorporated with rear park distance sensors with visual display. At the same time, the base variant lacks several aspects but owner can add many more exterior and interior features for their convenience. In addition to these, it also has rear view camera, navigation system, i-Pad holder, rear seat entertainment system, Meridian signature reference audio system, television tuner, TFT virtual instrument panel, Grained leather seats, seat back storage, luggage compartment mat, rigid load space protector and so on. On the other hand, we can also customize the exteriors by adding illuminated tread plates, mud flaps, stainless steel exhaust finisher, stylish body graphics, hood decals, side protection tubes, panoramic sun roof, xenon headlamps with LED signature, contrast roof and primed mirror caps. In addition to these, we can also add it with an off-road package, which includes twin speed transfer box, automatic terrain response system and dynamic program including torque vectoring by braking.Ed's Take:\u000a This is the best handling Land Rover ever made. Land Rover also claims the same. So, we had no doubts about the handling characteristics of the Range Rover Sport.\u000a This SUV has a reliable braking and proficient suspension mechanism, which keeps it well balanced. In order to enhance the braking mechanism, the company has incorporated it with several advanced aspects like anti lock braking system along with electronic brake force distribution and emergency brake assist system. All its wheels are fitted with powerful disc brakes that are accompanied with high performance calipers. The company has also given this vehicle a cornering brake control, dynamic and roll stability control, electric parking brake and many other such features. On the other hand, the front and rear axles are assembled with a four corner air suspension system. It also has adaptive dynamic system that helps in reducing the impact of jerks and provide an pleasurable driving experience. It is also integrated a responsive power steering system with speed related function that makes it easy to handle even in peak traffic conditions.Ed's Take\u000a : The Range Rover Sport comes loaded with several safety features like multiple airbags, ABS, ESP, traction control, hill descent control etc.\u000a For giving a stress free driving experience to its occupants, the manufacturer has bestowed this Land Rover Range Rover Sport model series with a lot of crucial protective aspects. The braking mechanism is further augmented by ABS along with emergency brake assist function and electric parking brake. This SUV has 3-point ELR seat belts for all passengers along with driver seat belt reminder notification on instrument panel. It has eight airbags (side curtain, dual front and knee airbag for driver), front and rear parking aid, LED high mounted stop lamp, central locking system, powerful disc brakes, fog lights, high intensity xenon lamps and several other aspects. This sports utility vehicle has a rigid body structure, which comes with impact beams and enhances safety of the occupants in case of any crash. It has an advanced engine immobilizer with volumetric alarm system that safeguards the vehicle from theft and any unauthorized entry. The company has also given innovative aspects like terrain response system (manual in diesel variants and automatic in petrol trim), which reduces the efforts of driver and improves the performance. It also has hill descent control, hill start assist, roll stability control and electronic traction control system. All these features put together makes it one of the safest vehicle in its segment.The neatly carved wheels arches are fitted with an elegant set of 20-inch, 5-split spoke alloy wheels, which enhances the look of its side profile. These rims are further equipped with high performance tubeless radial tyres, which makes it reliable for off-roading. The company has also given a full size spare wheel, which is affixed in the boot compartment with all other tools required for changing a flat tyre. It is a standard features across all the variants. 1. Spacious internal cabin with good seating arrangement.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a2. Fuel economy of diesel variants is quite satisfying.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a3. Advanced safety aspects adds to its advantage.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a4. Terrain response system is a big plus point.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a5. Decent ground clearance of 278mm is perfect for off-roading.  1. Base variant lack panoramic sun roof.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a2. Navigation system can be added.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a3. Off-road package is available in petrol variant only.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a4. Diesel engine noise and harshness can be reduced.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a5. Fuel economy of petrol trim is not up to the mark.
